modules.description: This structure provides dynamic arrays that automatically resize using a dummy value to manage unused memory slots, supporting efficient in-place modifications. Operations include stack-like appending (with amortized constant-time complexity), element access, slicing, iteration with indices, mapping to new arrays, and folding over elements, all while maintaining controlled memory usage. It is particularly suited for implementing stacks with improved cache locality, handling variable-sized data streams, and scenarios requiring predictable memory behavior through explicit dummy value management.
